b-2 leading-snug\",\"children\":\"India-US Relations: From Nuclear Deal to Critical Technology Partnership\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4 line-clamp-2\",\"children\":\"The India-US strategic partnership has deepened across defence, technology, trade, and people-to-people ties over the past two decades, driven by shared concerns about China's rise and converging geopolitical interests.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-4 text-xs text-gray-500\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"The Breakdown Editorial\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":[16,\" min\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-amber-500/80\",\"children\":[91,\"% evidence\"]}]]}]]}]\n1d:[\"$\",\"$L9\",\"india-ev-paradox\",{\"href\":\"/story/india-ev-paradox\",\"className\":\"group block p-6 bg-[#151515] rounded-lg border border-[#2A2A2A] hover:border-amber-500/50 transition-colors\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold border bg-gray-800/50 text-gray-300 border border-gray-700 \",\"children\":[false,false,\"environment\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors mb-2 leading-snug\",\"children\":\"India's EV Paradox: Rising Sales, Stalled Charging, and the ₹4 Lakh Crore Battery Import Bill\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4 line-clamp-2\",\"children\":\"EV sales have grown 4x in three years, but India's public charging network stands at only 26% of the official target. Meanwhile, the country's battery import bill is projected to hit ₹4 lakh crore by 2030 — creating a strategic vulnerability as deep as the oil dependency EVs were meant to solve.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-4 text-xs text-gray-500\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"The Breakdown Editorial\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":[14,\" min\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-amber-500/80\",\"children\":[88,\"% evidence\"]}]]}]]}]\n1e:[\"$\",\"$L9\",\"electoral-bonds\",{\"href\":\"/story/electoral-bonds\",\"className\":\"group block p-6 bg-[#151515] rounded-lg border border-[#2A2A2A] hover:border-amber-500/50 transition-colors\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold border bg-gray-800/50 text-gray-300 border border-gray-700 \",\"children\":[false,false,\"policy\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors mb-2 leading-snug\",\"children\":\"Electoral Bonds: The ₹12,769 Crore Anonymous Donation Scheme the Supreme Court Struck Down\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4 line-clamp-2\",\"children\":\"Electoral Bonds were meant to clean up political funding. Instead, they created the most opaque campaign finance system in Indian history — ₹12,769 crore in anonymous donations, 47.5% flowing to the BJP, with shell companies and contractors under investigation pouring ₹4,200+ crore into ruling party coffers. The Supreme Court struck down the scheme in February 2024.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-4 text-xs text-gray-500\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"The Breakdown Editorial\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":[16,\" min\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-amber-500/80\",\"children\":[95,\"% evidence\"]}]]}]]}]\n1f:[\"$\",\"$L9\",\"india-5g-rollout\",{\"href\":\"/story/india-5g-rollout\",\"className\":\"group block p-6 bg-[#151515] rounded-lg border border-[#2A2A2A] hover:border-amber-500/50 transition-colors\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null